---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const lastUpdated = '12 June 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Studio Conduct Policy — Moose"
  description="The Moose Studio Conduct Policy setting out the baseline conduct rules and expectations for Participating Studios using Moose, operated by Blubby Pty Ltd (trading as Moose Club). Read together with the Moose Studio Terms of Use."
>
  <header class="legal-nav">
    <div class="container legal-nav__inner">
      <a href="/" class="legal-nav__brand" aria-label="Moose home">
        <img src="/brand/logo/moose-wordmark-twotone.svg" alt="Moose" class="legal-nav__logo" />
      </a>
      <a href="/" class="legal-nav__back">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="14" height="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M19 12H5M11 18l-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
        <span>Back to home</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main id="main" class="legal">
    <div class="container legal__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--ink">Moose Club</p>
      <h1 class="display-s legal__title">Studio Conduct Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal__meta">
        Blubby Pty Ltd ABN 11 690 645 106 trading as Moose Club<br />
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>

      <div class="legal__body">
        <h2>Part A — General terms</h2>

        <h3>Purpose</h3>
        <p>
          This Studio Conduct Policy sets out the baseline conduct rules and expectations that apply to
          Participating Studios when they use Moose, form Partnerships, host Visiting Users or interact
          with Moose, Partner Studios, Members, Moose Users and Visiting Users.
        </p>
        <p>
          The purpose of this policy is to help keep the Moose network fair, reliable and trusted,
          while allowing each Participating Studio to continue operating its own business, venue,
          classes and member relationships.
        </p>

        <h3>Relationship with Moose Studio Terms of Use</h3>
        <p>
          This Studio Conduct Policy applies under the <a href="/studio-terms">Moose Studio Terms of
          Use</a> and should be read together with those terms.
        </p>
        <p>
          Capitalised terms used in this Studio Conduct Policy have the meaning given to them in the
          Moose Studio Terms of Use unless the context requires otherwise.
        </p>
        <p>
          By participating in Moose, each Participating Studio agrees to comply with this Studio
          Conduct Policy, as updated, provided or made available by Moose from time to time.
        </p>

        <h3>Application to Participating Studios</h3>
        <p>
          This Studio Conduct Policy applies to each Participating Studio in connection with its use of
          Moose, participation in Partnerships, hosting or attendance of Crossover Sessions,
          interactions with Moose, and interactions with other Participating Studios, Members, Moose
          Users and Visiting Users.
        </p>

        <h3>Updates to this policy</h3>
        <p>Moose may update this Studio Conduct Policy from time to time.</p>
        <p>Any updated Studio Conduct Policy applies to each Participating Studio once published, made available or provided by Moose.</p>

        <h3>Breaches of this policy</h3>
        <p>Breaches of this Studio Conduct Policy may be notified, managed and enforced in accordance with the Moose Studio Terms of Use.</p>

        <h3>Inconsistency</h3>
        <p>If there is any inconsistency between this Studio Conduct Policy and the Moose Studio Terms of Use, the Moose Studio Terms of Use prevail to the extent of the inconsistency.</p>

        <h2>Part B — Studio obligations</h2>

        <h3>Baseline conduct</h3>
        <p>Each Participating Studio must participate in Moose in good faith and in a manner consistent with the purpose and proper operation of Moose.</p>
        <p>Participating Studios must act reasonably and cooperatively in relation to Partnerships, Crossover Sessions, Visiting Users, booking issues, attendance issues, incidents and operational matters connected with Moose.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio must not engage in conduct that undermines the proper operation of Moose, the Platform, a Partnership, this Studio Conduct Policy or the confidence of other Participating Studios in the Moose network.</p>

        <h3>Communication and availability</h3>
        <p>A Participating Studio must be reasonably contactable by Moose and its Partner Studios in relation to any Partnership.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio must respond within a reasonable time to operational queries, booking issues, attendance issues, Visiting User issues, Partnership issues and other matters reasonably connected with Moose.</p>

        <h3>Bookings and Crossover Sessions</h3>
        <p>A Participating Studio must honour valid Crossover Session bookings made through Moose, subject to the Moose Studio Terms of Use, this Studio Conduct Policy and the way the Platform is configured, operated and made available by Moose.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio must not refuse, cancel, disadvantage or treat a Visiting User unfairly merely because the booking was made through Moose.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio must ensure that its Studio Personnel understand how to identify and manage valid Crossover Session bookings.</p>

        <h3>Treatment of Visiting Users</h3>
        <p>A Participating Studio must treat Visiting Users respectfully, fairly and consistently with the purpose of Moose.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio must not treat a Visiting User unfairly merely because they are attending through Moose or because their Home Studio is another Participating Studio.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio may require Visiting Users to comply with its applicable venue rules, terms, policies, waivers, safety requirements and reasonable directions, provided those requirements are applied reasonably and consistently.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio should raise any material issue involving a Visiting User with Moose where the issue may affect the Visiting User's access to Moose, the safety of participants, the operation of a Partnership or the integrity of the Moose network.</p>

        <h3>No undermining Partner Studios</h3>
        <p>A Participating Studio must not actively solicit, induce or specifically target a Visiting User accessed through Moose for the purpose of encouraging that Visiting User to cancel, reduce or transfer their membership with their Home Studio.</p>
        <p>A Participating Studio must not use Moose, a Partnership, Visiting User information, Member information, booking information or Platform information to undermine another Participating Studio's relationship with its Members.</p>

        <h3>Data and information use</h3>
        <p>A Participating Studio must only use Moose data, Platform data, Member data, Moose User data, Visiting User data, Partner Studio information and Participating Studio information for the purposes of participating in Moose and as permitted by Moose.</p>

        <h3>Cooperation with Moose and Partner Studios</h3>
        <p>A Participating Studio must reasonably cooperate with Moose and Partner Studios in relation to Partnerships, Crossover Sessions, Visiting Users, booking issues, attendance issues, operational queries and other matters reasonably connected with Moose.</p>

        <h3>Studio Personnel</h3>
        <p>A Participating Studio must ensure its Studio Personnel are appropriately informed and familiar with Moose to the extent relevant to their role, including how to manage Crossover Session bookings and deal with Visiting Users.</p>

        <h3>Staff Crossover Access</h3>
        <p>Where Staff Crossover Access is enabled through Moose, the Participating Studio must ensure its relevant Studio Personnel use that access appropriately and in accordance with the purpose of Moose.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="legal-foot">
    <div class="container legal-foot__inner">
      <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Moose Club. Made in Australia.</span>
      <a href="/">Return home</a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Slim header — section anchors don't exist on this route, so this page
     ships its own minimal nav instead of reusing MSNav. Mirrors terms.astro. */
  .legal-nav {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
    backdrop-filter: blur(14px) saturate(140%);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(14px) saturate(140%);
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
  }
  .legal-nav__inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    height: 72px;
  }
  .legal-nav__logo { display: block; height: 30px; width: auto; }
  .legal-nav__back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    padding: 9px 14px;
    border-radius: var(--r-sm);
    transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out), background var(--dur-fast);
  }
  .legal-nav__back:hover { color: var(--ink); background: var(--navy-50); }

  .legal { padding-block: clamp(48px, 7vw, 88px); background: var(--paper); }
  .legal__inner { max-width: 760px; }
  .legal__title { color: var(--navy); margin-top: 18px; }
  .legal__meta {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
  }

  .legal__body { margin-top: 40px; }
  .legal__body h2 {
    font-size: clamp(19px, 1.8vw, 24px);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-top: 44px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .legal__body h3 {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-top: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .legal__body p {
    font-size: 15.5px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .legal__body strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; }
  .legal__body a {
    color: var(--pink);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-foot {
    background: var(--navy-900);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    padding-block: 28px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .legal-foot__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .legal-foot a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
    transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
  }
  .legal-foot a:hover { color: #fff; }
</style>
